===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{weaponry}} A long-bladed [[weapon]] having a handle and sometimes a [[hilt]] and designed to stab, cut or [[slash]]. <!-- This is encyclopedic: It was sheathed in a [[scabbard]]. It was originally a [[melée]] weapon that was used in serious combat, but now is mostly used in sports and for ceremonies, and is viewed as one of the most noble weapons.-->
#* '''1591''', William Shakespeare, ''Henry VI'', Part III, Act II, Scene II, line 59.
#*: [[unsheathe|Unsheathe]] your [[sword]] and [[dub]] him [[presently]].
#* '''1786''', Francis Grose, ''A Treatise on Ancient Armour and Weapons'', page 49.
#*: Some [[sword]]s were also made [[solely]] to [[thrust]], and some only to [[cut]]; others were [[equally]] [[adapt]]ed for both.
# Someone [[paid]] to [[handle]] a sword.
# {{context|tarot}} A [[suit]] in the minor [[arcana]] in [[tarot]].
# {{context|tarot}} A [[card]] of this suit.

